<template><div><h1 id="algolia-autocomplete-core" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#algolia-autocomplete-core" aria-hidden="true">#</a> @algolia/autocomplete-core</h1>
<p>The <a href="https://www.algolia.com/doc/ui-libraries/autocomplete/api-reference/autocomplete-core/createAutocomplete" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><code v-pre>autocomplete-core</code><ExternalLinkIcon/></a> package is the foundation of Autocomplete. It exposes primitives to build an autocomplete experience.</p>
<p>You likely don’t need to use this package directly unless you’re building a <a href="https://www.algolia.com/doc/ui-libraries/autocomplete/guides/creating-a-renderer" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">renderer<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>.</p>
